Dear Beverly,

Action for Children in the interim
As you know, the 2009 legislative session has ended. The N.C. General Assembly will reconvene on May 12, 2010. Action for Children will be working hard during the interim to move our action items forward:
* Health Insurance for All Children: We will continue to work for health insurance reform on the federal level, while urging our state leaders to put more funding towards N.C. Health Choice, in order to cover more of North Carolina's children.
*  Juvenile Justice: We will be working with stakeholders (policymakers, advocates, communities and families) to continue moving forward on our Raise the Age campaign, through community forums, fact sheets and issue briefs, meetings with key leaders and more.
*  Economic Security: We will be providing technical assistance to the N.C. Financial Literacy Council and holding community forums around the state to get community input on asset development policies to help build an assets agenda for the state in 2010.
