GRACIE’ JOURNEY TO HER EAR by her mother Mary











My beautiful daughter who was born with Hemifacial Microsomia. The day Graci was born was the happiest day of my life. She came into this world just as I had imagined....beautiful!!! She was diagnosed with having over 6 craniofacial birth defects all on one side of her face.

She has already undergone four surgeries to correct her cleft lip and cleft palate. She was also born with microtia which wasn't noted on the ultrasound so it was a complete shock to my husband and I. Microtia is a birth defect of the ear. It is where the ear didn't form properly in the womb causing her to be born with only the ear lope. She can't hear out of that ear and it looks quite different from the other ear. It has been very difficult dealing with that for the past six years but with God's Grace and strength we have overcome every frustration and trial that has come our way.

We have now reached the point where she is having ear reconstruction. She has already had the first stage where we traveled to California to see Dr. Burt Brent who is a plastic surgeon who only does ear reconstruction. He actually craves the ear from the child's very own rib cartilage causing it to grow as they grow. It is amazing what he has already done and we are so excited to have gotten this process started. She will have four more surgeries over the next year before her ear is complete.

The sad thing to this story is that insurance has denied Graci her ear. She deserves an ear like her brother and she has always wanted "two matching ears". My family will make this dream come true for her regardless of the expense.

However, we live in such a caring and thoughtful community that may organizations, families, businesses have already given to Graci's Ear Fund. I can't express my gratitude enough to everyone for their thoughts and prayers during this challenge. God has a plan for Graci and it is getting her what she deserves.

I ask you to join us as we journey through this amazing journey watching a brave little girl get her ear she has been dreaming of!!!












