Cuts not only in the education budget but in the Departments of Health and Human Services and Juvenile Justice have dramatically cut services to young people and afterschool programs.  Some of the major impact areas on young people and their families include:

* The Support Our Students (SOS) and Governor's One-on-One Mentoring programs that provided afterschool programs for nearly 15,000 young people are eliminated.
* Eckerd Wilderness Camps are cut by $2.7m, including closure of 2 of the 7 camps.
