Lurasidone is an atypical antipsychotic discovered and developed by DSP with a unique chemical structure. Lurasidone has high affinities for dopamine D2, serotonin 5-HT7, 5-HT2A, 5-HT1A, and noradrenalin Î±2C receptors and minimal-to-no affinity for histamine H1 or cholinergic M1 receptors.


